
Aptitude /Reasoning

*************************************************

A. Core Java

OOP Concepts: Encapsulation, Abstraction, Inheritance, Polymorphism

Collections Framework: List, Set, Map, Queue, Iterator

Exception Handling: try/catch/finally, custom exceptions

Java 8+ Features: Lambda, Streams, Optional, Method references

B. Advanced Java

Multithreading: Thread, Runnable, synchronized, ExecutorService

Streams API: map, filter, reduce, collect

File I/O: IO & NIO

Socket Programming: TCP/UDP

C. Spring Core

Beans & Lifecycle

Dependency Injection (DI): Constructor/Setter

AOP: @Aspect, @Before, @After

Annotation-based configuration: @Component, @Bean, @Autowired

D. JavaScript

Variables: var, let, const

Data types, Operators

Arrays & Objects

DOM Manipulation

Fetch API & AJAX

JSON Handling

E. Spring WebFlux

Reactive Programming Basics

Mono / Flux

Reactive REST APIs

Backpressure & Event-loop



*************************************************


Topic-wise Interview Questions & Answers

Core Java Q&A

OOP principles, ArrayList vs LinkedList, HashMap internals, Exception handling, Java 8 features

Advanced Java Q&A

Multithreading, synchronized, Streams API, File I/O, Socket programming

Spring Core Q&A

DI, AOP, Bean annotations, differences between @Component/@Bean

JavaScript Q&A

var/let/const, == vs ===, Fetch API, JSON parsing

Spring WebFlux Q&A

Reactive programming, Mono/Flux, WebFlux vs MVC

